headline: CEG, OKLO, and SMR Get Set to Power the AI Boom via Nuclear Energy
summary: The nuclear energy sector is experiencing a resurgence unseen in decades, driven largely by its potential to power the burgeoning AI revolution. Major technology companies such as Meta (META), Microsoft (MSFT), and Alphabet (GOOGL) are competing to secure reliable energy sources for their expanding data centers, and nuclear power’s clean, consistent output has positioned it as a key player in this race. Leading this revival are three companies—Constellation Energy (CEG), Oklo (OKLO), and NuScale
